          "id": "cue-bf2b09e683eb",
          "atMs": 250,
          "text": "When sprite positions, terrain, enemies, and pickups live as setters in Java, nobody can see the level until it runs. Moving art forces a rebuild, designers cannot work safely, and behavior becomes tangled with layout.",
          "caption": "When sprite positions, terrain, enemies, and pickups live as setters in Java, nobody can see the level until it runs. Moving art forces a rebuild, designers cannot work safely, and behavior becomes tangled with layout."
